<Content>A great oasis Staying at the Hotel Royak in the Zona Rosa of Mexico City is a near perfect experience. As a business traveller the HR is excellent quality for price, friendly, delightful stay with spacious comfortable rooms, excellent meals with two restaurants (one with a breakfast buffet). For the cigar smokers, there is a cigar bar attached with high quality low price Royal brand cigars. Free internet (either wireless or wired, depending on the room). An excellent indoor-outdoor penthouse bar and even a gym and pool.What is not to love. A secure ATM about fifty feet down the block.Walk outside and you immediately understand the oasis concept. Zona Rosa, at one time a great tourist district has become everything that you may not want, especially as a solo traveller. Sleezy harassment every step of evey block. Out on the street after 6:00 PM is a major challenge. Dive for one of the secure taxis and you are fine, but you better make sure it is secure.One fatiques of this very quickly.If you plan to come to Mexico City for business and you have to stay in the Zona Rosa area, this is a great place to stay. 
