<Author>sylin2
<Content>For $74 a night, a good deal I was able to get a $74 per night rate on Orbitz, a savings over the rack rate which was around $124. The hotel is located close to a metro stop. I used the metro to get around town during the day; clean, easy to navigate, quick and safe (just be aware of your surroundings as you should be in any large city). It is also centrally located so you can walk to other areas of town, if you are an urban walker. Zona Rosa was not very quaint but not objectionable. There are restaurants and bars within walking distance. As mentioned in other reviews, the beds were very firm but not uncomfortable, in my opinion. One benefit of staying in a hotel with many rooms (about 160, if I remember correctly) was that I was able to check-in early after a red-eye flight. I imagine that smaller hotels are far less likely to have empty, available rooms at 6:30 am. All in all, I was pleased by the location and cleanliness of the Royal Zona Rosa... especially for the price I paid. 
